description: Angular frontend conventions for standalone components and signals
globs: frontend/src/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Angular + Signals Rules

- Use standalone components only; do not add NgModules.
- Use `signal()` and `computed()` for state; do not introduce NgRx.
- Keep feature-first organization under `features/<feature>/...`.
- Prefer lazy-loaded routes for feature pages.
- Keep components focused: move reusable state logic to `state/` and pure helpers to `utils/`.

# TypeScript Quality

- Keep functions small and explicit in naming.
- Avoid `any`; use typed DTOs/interfaces for API and UI state.
- Add short English comments only where logic is not obvious.
